The paper discusses the analysis of the Bitcoin transaction network using complex networks analysis techniques, which falls under the scope of social network analysis (cs.SOC) and database systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the issue of user anonymity and proposes a method to re-identify multiple addresses belonging to a same user, which falls under the scope of cybersecurity (cs.CR) and cybercrime (cs.CYBER). Finally, the paper uses community detection algorithms to identify groups of addresses belonging to the same user, which falls under the scope of computational social science (cs.SI).
